<div class = "grid-row">
  <div class= "column-whole">
   <h1 class="heading-xlarge"> Race disparity in the public sector </h1>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="grid-row">
  <div class="column-two-thirds">

    <p>
      Government departments measure how people from different races access public services.
    </p>

    <p>
      This data will help to reflect the realities of people living in the UK, and feed into policy issues relating to race disparity.
    </p>

    <p>
      Over time, more information will be collected and reported here.
    </p>

    <h3 class="heading-medium">
      Browse the available data
    </h3>

    <p > You can browse all the available data or find something more specific using the options and filters below. </p>

    <div id="navigation-tabs" class="homepage">
      <ul class = "tabs-nav">
        <li id="<%= HomepageController::TOPIC %>-selector" class="selected">
          <a href="#">Topic</a>
        </li>

        <li id="<%=HomepageController::LOCATION %>-selector">
          <a href="#">Location</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="grid-row radios-container" id="topic-section">
  <div class="column-two-thirds">
    <input type="hidden" name="filter_type" value="<%=HomepageController::TOPIC%>">
    <p>Select one of the options below.</p>

    <span class="heading-small"><a href="/topics/all">All</a></span>
    <p> See the full list of data available </p>

    <% TaxonomyLevel.homepage.taxonomy_levels.each_with_index do |topic, index| %>
        <span class="heading-small"><a href="/topics/<%= topic.id %>"><%= topic.display_name %></a></span>
        <p> <%= topic.description %></p>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="grid-row radios-container" id="location-section">
  <div class= "column-two-thirds">

    <p>
    Information is collected differently, depending on the organisation and the reason for measuring it. Some of the information we publish on race disparity is only available at a national level, and some is available at a more detailed level (e.g. for a local authority, postcode, or for a specific school or prison).
    </p>

    <p>
    You can find information and data on race disparity for a specific area - where the data is available at that level. If it isn't available, you may need to broaden your search to a larger regional area.
    </p>

    <div class= "location-search">
      <label for="search-main"><h4 class="heading-small">Explore by area:</h4>

        <input type="search" id="search-main">
      </label>
      <button type="submit" class="button"> Search </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

